4. Orthogonal mapping

You also mentioned applying patterns orthogonally.

That means mapping the same pattern into a different dimension of interpretation.

Example pattern:

containment

Possible mappings:

domain	example
physical	water in cup
logical	idea inside argument
social	person in organization
computing	data inside file

Same structure, different interpretation layer.

